{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":462,"text":"As humans, it's in our nature"},{"time":2161,"text":"to want to improve our health \nand minimize our suffering."},{"time":5455,"text":"Whatever life throws at us,"},{"time":7122,"text":"whether it's cancer, diabetes, heart disease,"},{"time":9587,"text":"or even broken bones, we want to try and get better."},{"time":12779,"text":"Now I'm head of a biomaterials lab,"},{"time":15262,"text":"and I'm really fascinated by the way that humans"},{"time":18002,"text":"have used materials in really creative ways"},{"time":20470,"text":"in the body over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23214,"text":"Take, for example, this beautiful blue nacre shell."},{"time":26860,"text":"This was actually used by the Mayans"},{"time":28742,"text":"as an artificial tooth replacement."},{"time":32281,"text":"We're not quite sure why they did it."},{"time":33914,"text":"It's hard. It's durable."},{"time":36490,"text":"But it also had other very nice properties."},{"time":40608,"text":"In fact, when they put it into the jawbone,"},{"time":42888,"text":"it could integrate into the jaw,"},{"time":45795,"text":"and we know now with very sophisticated"},{"time":47893,"text":"imaging technologies"},{"time":49566,"text":"that part of that integration comes from the fact"},{"time":51915,"text":"that this material is designed"},{"time":53602,"text":"in a very specific way, has a beautiful chemistry,"},{"time":56421,"text":"has a beautiful architecture."},{"time":58649,"text":"And I think in many ways we can sort of think"},{"time":60401,"text":"of the use of the blue nacre shell and the Mayans"},{"time":63408,"text":"as the first real application"},{"time":64928,"text":"of the bluetooth technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67223,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68685,"text":"But if we move on and think throughout history"},{"time":73078,"text":"how people have used different \nmaterials in the body,"},{"time":76062,"text":"very often it's been physicians"},{"time":77776,"text":"that have been quite creative."},{"time":79168,"text":"They've taken things off the shelf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81136,"text":"One of my favorite examples"},{"time":83036,"text":"is that of Sir Harold Ridley,"},{"time":86278,"text":"who was a famous ophthalmologist,"},{"time":88416,"text":"or at least became a famous ophthalmologist."},{"time":90984,"text":"And during World War II, what he would see"},{"time":92911,"text":"would be pilots coming back from their missions,"},{"time":95763,"text":"and he noticed that within their eyes"},{"time":97515,"text":"they had shards of small bits of material"},{"time":100455,"text":"lodged within the eye,"},{"time":101975,"text":"but the very interesting thing about it"},{"time":103674,"text":"was that material, actually, wasn't causing"},{"time":105967,"text":"any inflammatory response."},{"time":107980,"text":"So he looked into this, and he figured out"},{"time":110319,"text":"that actually that material was little shards of plastic"},{"time":112923,"text":"that were coming from the canopy of the Spitfires."},{"time":115662,"text":"And this led him to propose that material"},{"time":118063,"text":"as a new material for intraocular lenses."},{"time":120825,"text":"It's called PMMA, and it's now used"},{"time":122930,"text":"in millions of people every year"},{"time":124732,"text":"and helps in preventing cataracts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127501,"text":"And that example, I think, is a really nice one,"},{"time":129810,"text":"because it helps remind us that in the early days,"},{"time":132245,"text":"people often chose materials"},{"time":134198,"text":"because they were bioinert."},{"time":136083,"text":"Their very purpose was to \nperform a mechanical function."},{"time":139595,"text":"You'd put them in the body"},{"time":141045,"text":"and you wouldn't get an adverse response."},{"time":143209,"text":"And what I want to show you is that"},{"time":144877,"text":"in regenerative medicine,"},{"time":146258,"text":"we've really shifted away from that idea"},{"time":148082,"text":"of taking a bioinert material."},{"time":149995,"text":"We're actually actively looking for materials"},{"time":152284,"text":"that will be bioactive, that will interact with the body,"},{"time":155252,"text":"and that furthermore we can put in the body,"},{"time":157579,"text":"they'll have their function,"},{"time":159028,"text":"and then they'll dissolve away over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163578,"text":"If we look at this schematic,"},{"time":165511,"text":"this is showing you what we think of"},{"time":167112,"text":"as the typical tissue-engineering approach."},{"time":169249,"text":"We have cells there, typically from the patient."},{"time":172093,"text":"We can put those onto a material,"},{"time":173975,"text":"and we can make that material \nvery complex if we want to,"},{"time":176708,"text":"and we can then grow that up in the lab"},{"time":178878,"text":"or we can put it straight back into the patient."},{"time":181393,"text":"And this is an approach that's \nused all over the world,"},{"time":183844,"text":"including in our lab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187367,"text":"But one of the things that's really important"},{"time":189824,"text":"when we're thinking about stem cells"},{"time":191702,"text":"is that obviously stem cells \ncan be many different things,"},{"time":194281,"text":"and they want to be many different things,"},{"time":196045,"text":"and so we want to make sure that the environment"},{"time":197921,"text":"we put them into has enough information"},{"time":200271,"text":"so that they can become the right sort"},{"time":202267,"text":"of specialist tissue."},{"time":204953,"text":"And if we think about the different types of tissues"},{"time":208016,"text":"that people are looking at regenerating"},{"time":210035,"text":"all over the world, in all the \ndifferent labs in the world,"},{"time":212346,"text":"there's pretty much every tissue you can think of."},{"time":215282,"text":"And actually, the structure of those tissues"},{"time":216904,"text":"is quite different, and it's going to really depend"},{"time":219518,"text":"on whether your patient has any underlying disease,"},{"time":221936,"text":"other conditions, in terms of how"},{"time":224986,"text":"you're going to regenerate your tissue,"},{"time":226547,"text":"and you're going to need to think about the materials"},{"time":228532,"text":"you're going to use really carefully,"},{"time":230586,"text":"their biochemistry, their mechanics,"},{"time":232311,"text":"and many other properties as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236049,"text":"Our tissues all have very \ndifferent abilities to regenerate,"},{"time":239349,"text":"and here we see poor Prometheus,"},{"time":241091,"text":"who made a rather tricky career choice"},{"time":244184,"text":"and was punished by the Greek gods."},{"time":247118,"text":"He was tied to a rock, and an eagle would come"},{"time":249439,"text":"every day to eat his liver."},{"time":251042,"text":"But of course his liver would regenerate every day,"},{"time":253309,"text":"and so day after day he was punished"},{"time":255581,"text":"for eternity by the gods."},{"time":261378,"text":"And liver will regenerate in this very nice way,"},{"time":265258,"text":"but actually if we think of other tissues,"},{"time":267034,"text":"like cartilage, for example,"},{"time":268803,"text":"even the simplest nick and you're going to find it"},{"time":270859,"text":"really difficult to regenerate your cartilage."},{"time":273302,"text":"So it's going to be very different from tissue to tissue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276416,"text":"Now, bone is somewhere in between,"},{"time":279216,"text":"and this is one of the tissues \nthat we work on a lot in our lab."},{"time":282116,"text":"And bone is actually quite good at repairing."},{"time":284100,"text":"It has to be. We've probably all had fractures"},{"time":286113,"text":"at some point or other."},{"time":287925,"text":"And one of the ways that you can think"},{"time":290082,"text":"about repairing your fracture"},{"time":291771,"text":"is this procedure here, called \nan iliac crest harvest."},{"time":294598,"text":"And what the surgeon might do"},{"time":296264,"text":"is take some bone from your iliac crest,"},{"time":299459,"text":"which is just here,"},{"time":300837,"text":"and then transplant that \nsomewhere else in the body."},{"time":303361,"text":"And it actually works really well,"},{"time":304961,"text":"because it's your own bone,"},{"time":306460,"text":"and it's well vascularized,"},{"time":307694,"text":"which means it's got a really good blood supply."},{"time":310063,"text":"But the problem is, there's\nonly so much you can take,"},{"time":312846,"text":"and also when you do that operation,"},{"time":315769,"text":"your patients might actually have significant pain"},{"time":318308,"text":"in that defect site even two \nyears after the operation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321549,"text":"So what we were thinking is,"},{"time":323435,"text":"there's a tremendous need \nfor bone repair, of course,"},{"time":326584,"text":"but this iliac crest-type approach"},{"time":329071,"text":"really has a lot of limitations to it,"},{"time":331503,"text":"and could we perhaps recreate"},{"time":333737,"text":"the generation of bone within the body"},{"time":335906,"text":"on demand and then be able to transplant it"},{"time":339221,"text":"without these very, very painful aftereffects"},{"time":344126,"text":"that you would have with the iliac crest harvest?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":347809,"text":"And so this is what we did, and the way we did it"},{"time":350471,"text":"was by coming back to this typical tissue-engineering approach"},{"time":353809,"text":"but actually thinking about it rather differently."},{"time":356196,"text":"And we simplified it a lot,"},{"time":358115,"text":"so we got rid of a lot of these steps."},{"time":360166,"text":"We got rid of the need to \nharvest cells from the patient,"},{"time":362540,"text":"we got rid of the need to put \nin really fancy chemistries,"},{"time":365457,"text":"and we got rid of the need"},{"time":367149,"text":"to culture these scaffolds in the lab."},{"time":369977,"text":"And what we really focused on"},{"time":372156,"text":"was our material system and making it quite simple,"},{"time":375905,"text":"but because we used it in a really clever way,"},{"time":378230,"text":"we were able to generate enormous amounts of bone"},{"time":380877,"text":"using this approach."},{"time":382523,"text":"So we were using the body"},{"time":384276,"text":"as really the catalyst to help us"},{"time":386396,"text":"to make lots of new bone."},{"time":388939,"text":"And it's an approach that we call"},{"time":390522,"text":"the in vivo bioreactor, and we were able to make"},{"time":393333,"text":"enormous amounts of bone using this approach."},{"time":395819,"text":"And I'll talk you through this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397058,"text":"So what we do is,"},{"time":399538,"text":"in humans, we all have a layer of stem cells"},{"time":401881,"text":"on the outside of our long bones."},{"time":403769,"text":"That layer is called the periosteum."},{"time":405472,"text":"And that layer is actually normally"},{"time":407760,"text":"very, very tightly bound to the underlying bone,"},{"time":410409,"text":"and it's got stem cells in it."},{"time":411841,"text":"Those stem cells are really important"},{"time":413260,"text":"in the embryo when it develops,"},{"time":415069,"text":"and they also sort of wake up if you have a fracture"},{"time":417311,"text":"to help you with repairing the bone."},{"time":420172,"text":"So we take that periosteum layer"},{"time":422265,"text":"and we developed a way to inject underneath it"},{"time":425255,"text":"a liquid that then, within 30 seconds,"},{"time":428071,"text":"would turn into quite a rigid gel"},{"time":429816,"text":"and can actually lift the\nperiosteum away from the bone."},{"time":433069,"text":"So it creates, in essence, an artificial cavity"},{"time":436757,"text":"that is right next to both the bone"},{"time":440304,"text":"but also this really rich layer of stem cells."},{"time":444005,"text":"And we go in through a pinhole incision"},{"time":445617,"text":"so that no other cells from the body can get in,"},{"time":448570,"text":"and what happens is that that\nartificial in vivo bioreactor cavity"},{"time":453362,"text":"can then lead to the proliferation of these stem cells,"},{"time":456038,"text":"and they can form lots of new tissue,"},{"time":458124,"text":"and then over time, you can harvest that tissue"},{"time":460442,"text":"and use it elsewhere in the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463390,"text":"This is a histology slide"},{"time":465534,"text":"of what we see when we do that,"},{"time":467704,"text":"and essentially what we see"},{"time":470221,"text":"is very large amounts of bone."},{"time":471855,"text":"So in this picture, you can see the middle of the leg,"},{"time":474335,"text":"so the bone marrow,"},{"time":475836,"text":"then you can see the original bone,"},{"time":477640,"text":"and you can see where that original bone finishes,"},{"time":480496,"text":"and just to the left of that is the new bone"},{"time":483007,"text":"that's grown within that bioreactor cavity,"},{"time":485044,"text":"and you can actually make it even larger."},{"time":487475,"text":"And that demarcation that you can see"},{"time":490102,"text":"between the original bone and the new bone"},{"time":492453,"text":"acts as a very slight point of weakness,"},{"time":494466,"text":"so actually now the surgeon can come along,"},{"time":496600,"text":"can harvest away that new bone,"},{"time":498624,"text":"and the periosteum can grow back,"},{"time":500827,"text":"so you're left with the leg"},{"time":502696,"text":"in the same sort of state"},{"time":504246,"text":"as if you hadn't operated on it in the first place.\n"},{"time":506248,"text":"So it's very, very low in terms of after-pain"},{"time":510097,"text":"compared to an iliac crest harvest."},{"time":513952,"text":"And you can grow different amounts of bone"},{"time":516056,"text":"depending on how much gel you put in there,"},{"time":518075,"text":"so it really is an on demand sort of procedure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521277,"text":"Now, at the time that we did this,"},{"time":523479,"text":"this received a lot of attention in the press,"},{"time":526816,"text":"because it was a really nice way"},{"time":529247,"text":"of generating new bone,"},{"time":530713,"text":"and we got many, many contacts"},{"time":532708,"text":"from different people that \nwere interested in using this."},{"time":535326,"text":"And I'm just going to tell you,"},{"time":537115,"text":"sometimes those contacts are very strange,"},{"time":540068,"text":"slightly unexpected,"},{"time":541928,"text":"and the very most interesting,"},{"time":544990,"text":"let me put it that way, contact that I had,"},{"time":547275,"text":"was actually from a team of American footballers"},{"time":550486,"text":"that all wanted to have double-thickness skulls"},{"time":553866,"text":"made on their head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558156,"text":"And so you do get these kinds of contacts,"},{"time":560880,"text":"and of course, being British"},{"time":563497,"text":"and also growing up in France,"},{"time":565251,"text":"I tend to be very blunt,"},{"time":567393,"text":"and so I had to explain to them very nicely"},{"time":569434,"text":"that in their particular case,"},{"time":570909,"text":"there probably wasn't that much in there"},{"time":572923,"text":"to protect in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575911,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577481,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578734,"text":"So this was our approach,"},{"time":580589,"text":"and it was simple materials,"},{"time":582233,"text":"but we thought about it carefully."},{"time":584220,"text":"And actually we know that those cells"},{"time":585840,"text":"in the body, in the embryo, as they develop"},{"time":587978,"text":"can form a different kind of tissue, cartilage,"},{"time":591207,"text":"and so we developed a gel that was slightly different"},{"time":593762,"text":"in nature and slightly different chemistry,"},{"time":596181,"text":"put it in there, and we were able to get"},{"time":598328,"text":"100 percent cartilage instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600506,"text":"And this approach works really well, I think,"},{"time":602514,"text":"for pre-planned procedures,"},{"time":604996,"text":"but it's something you do have to pre-plan."},{"time":607868,"text":"So for other kinds of operations,"},{"time":610136,"text":"there's definitely a need for other"},{"time":611833,"text":"scaffold-based approaches."},{"time":614336,"text":"And when you think about designing"},{"time":616705,"text":"those other scaffolds, actually,"},{"time":618343,"text":"you need a really multi-disciplinary team."},{"time":620314,"text":"And so our team has chemists,"},{"time":622379,"text":"it has cell biologists, surgeons, physicists even,"},{"time":625756,"text":"and those people all come together"},{"time":627786,"text":"and we think really hard about \ndesigning the materials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630197,"text":"But we want to make them have enough information"},{"time":633163,"text":"that we can get the cells to do what we want,"},{"time":635317,"text":"but not be so complex as to make it difficult"},{"time":637694,"text":"to get to clinic."},{"time":639437,"text":"And so one of the things we think about a lot"},{"time":642188,"text":"is really trying to understand"},{"time":643983,"text":"the structure of the tissues in the body."},{"time":646360,"text":"And so if we think of bone,"},{"time":648020,"text":"obviously my own favorite tissue,"},{"time":650644,"text":"we zoom in, we can see,"},{"time":652201,"text":"even if you don't know anything \nabout bone structure,"},{"time":654083,"text":"it's beautifully organized, \nreally beautifully organized."},{"time":656628,"text":"We've lots of blood vessels in there."},{"time":658515,"text":"And if we zoom in again, we see that the cells"},{"time":660854,"text":"are actually surrounded by a 3D matrix"},{"time":663826,"text":"of nano-scale fibers, and they give a lot"},{"time":665997,"text":"of information to the cells."},{"time":668179,"text":"And if we zoom in again,"},{"time":669793,"text":"actually in the case of bone, the matrix"},{"time":671994,"text":"around the cells is beautifully organized"},{"time":674145,"text":"at the nano scale, and it's a hybrid material"},{"time":676612,"text":"that's part organic, part inorganic."},{"time":679196,"text":"And that's led to a whole field, really,"},{"time":681268,"text":"that has looked at developing materials"},{"time":683659,"text":"that have this hybrid kind of structure."},{"time":686407,"text":"And so I'm showing here just two examples"},{"time":689685,"text":"where we've made some materials\nthat have that sort of structure,"},{"time":692805,"text":"and you can really tailor it."},{"time":694243,"text":"You can see here a very squishy one"},{"time":696307,"text":"and now a material that's also \nthis hybrid sort of material"},{"time":700406,"text":"but actually has remarkable toughness,"},{"time":702369,"text":"and it's no longer brittle."},{"time":703829,"text":"And an inorganic material \nwould normally be really brittle,"},{"time":706285,"text":"and you wouldn't be able to have"},{"time":707725,"text":"that sort of strength and toughness in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709913,"text":"One other thing I want to quickly mention is that"},{"time":712402,"text":"many of the scaffolds we make \nare porous, and they have to be,"},{"time":715117,"text":"because you want blood vessels to grow in there."},{"time":717220,"text":"But the pores are actually oftentimes"},{"time":719097,"text":"much bigger than the cells,"},{"time":720390,"text":"and so even though it's 3D,"},{"time":722101,"text":"the cell might see it more \nas a slightly curved surface,"},{"time":725456,"text":"and that's a little bit unnatural."},{"time":727132,"text":"And so one of the things you can think about doing"},{"time":729380,"text":"is actually making scaffolds \nwith slightly different dimensions"},{"time":732528,"text":"that might be able to surround your cells in 3D"},{"time":735321,"text":"and give them a little bit more information."},{"time":737890,"text":"And there's a lot of work going \non in both of these areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741471,"text":"Now finally, I just want to talk a little bit about"},{"time":745440,"text":"applying this sort of thing to cardiovascular disease,"},{"time":748148,"text":"because this is a really big clinical problem."},{"time":751411,"text":"And one of the things that we know is that,"},{"time":754996,"text":"unfortunately, if you have a heart attack,"},{"time":757235,"text":"then that tissue can start to die,"},{"time":760137,"text":"and your outcome may not be very good over time."},{"time":763888,"text":"And it would be really great, actually,"},{"time":765598,"text":"if we could stop that dead tissue"},{"time":767517,"text":"either from dying or help it to regenerate."},{"time":771502,"text":"And there's lots and lots of stem \ncell trials going on worldwide,"},{"time":774750,"text":"and they use many different types of cells,"},{"time":776822,"text":"but one common theme that seems to be coming out"},{"time":779174,"text":"is that actually, very often, those cells will die"},{"time":782173,"text":"once you've implanted them."},{"time":783968,"text":"And you can either put them into the heart"},{"time":785843,"text":"or into the blood system,"},{"time":787863,"text":"but either way, we don't seem to be able"},{"time":790225,"text":"to get quite the right number of cells"},{"time":792092,"text":"getting to the location we want them to"},{"time":794334,"text":"and being able to deliver the sort of beautiful"},{"time":798828,"text":"cell regeneration that we would like to have"},{"time":801568,"text":"to get good clinical outcomes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804985,"text":"And so some of the things that we're thinking of,"},{"time":806968,"text":"and many other people in the field are thinking of,"},{"time":810089,"text":"are actually developing materials for that."},{"time":813095,"text":"But there's a difference here."},{"time":814714,"text":"We still need chemistry, we still need mechanics,"},{"time":816924,"text":"we still need really interesting topography,"},{"time":819595,"text":"and we still need really interesting \nways to surround the cells."},{"time":822243,"text":"But now, the cells also"},{"time":824754,"text":"would probably quite like a material"},{"time":826779,"text":"that's going to be able to be conductive,"},{"time":828797,"text":"because the cells themselves will respond very well"},{"time":833006,"text":"and will actually conduct signals \nbetween themselves."},{"time":836485,"text":"You can see them now"},{"time":838001,"text":"beating synchronously on these materials,"},{"time":840476,"text":"and that's a very, very exciting development"},{"time":843255,"text":"that's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845369,"text":"So just to wrap up, I'd like to actually say that"},{"time":850193,"text":"being able to work in this sort of field,"},{"time":852549,"text":"all of us that work in this field"},{"time":854203,"text":"that's not only super-exciting science,"},{"time":856712,"text":"but also has the potential"},{"time":858758,"text":"to impact on patients,"},{"time":860726,"text":"however big or small they are,"},{"time":863156,"text":"is really a great privilege."},{"time":864709,"text":"And so for that, I'd like to thank all of you as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867853,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869170,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}